<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-07-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="86" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                    <head>No. 82.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Parker</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-07-31"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 31,
                            1886</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 25.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received with pleasure and read with
                        keen interest Mr. George C. Foulk’s dispatch No. 308 of the third ultimo,
                        relative to the colony of American missionaries in Seôul, and the successful
                        prosecution of their good works.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>T. F. BAYARD.</signed></closer>
                </div>
            </body></text></TEI>